about.label: about
about.comment: The subject matter of the content.

acceptedAnswer.label: acceptedAnswer
acceptedAnswer.comment: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

acceptedOffer.label: acceptedOffer
acceptedOffer.comment: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

acceptedPaymentMethod.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
acceptedPaymentMethod.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

acceptsReservations.label: acceptsReservations
acceptsReservations.comment: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings Yes or No.

accessCode.label: accessCode
accessCode.comment: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

accessMode.label: accessMode
accessMode.comment: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

accessModeSufficient.label: accessModeSufficient
accessModeSufficient.comment: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

accessibilityAPI.label: accessibilityAPI
accessibilityAPI.comment: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

accessibilityControl.label: accessibilityControl
accessibilityControl.comment: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

accessibilityFeature.label: accessibilityFeature
accessibilityFeature.comment: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

accessibilityHazard.label: accessibilityHazard
accessibilityHazard.comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

accessibilitySummary.label: accessibilitySummary
accessibilitySummary.comment: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

accountId.label: accountId
accountId.comment: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

accountablePerson.label: accountablePerson
accountablePerson.comment: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

acquiredFrom.label: acquiredFrom
acquiredFrom.comment: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

actionAccessibilityRequirement.label: actionAccessibilityRequirement
actionAccessibilityRequirement.comment: A set of requirements that a must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specied, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

actionApplication.label: actionApplication
actionApplication.comment: An application that can complete the request.

actionOption.label: actionOption
actionOption.comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

actionPlatform.label: actionPlatform
actionPlatform.comment: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

actionStatus.label: actionStatus
actionStatus.comment: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

actor.label: actor
actor.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

actors.label: actors
actors.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

addOn.label: addOn
addOn.comment: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

additionalName.label: additionalName
additionalName.comment: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

additionalNumberOfGuests.label: additionalNumberOfGuests
additionalNumberOfGuests.comment: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

additionalProperty.label: additionalProperty
additionalProperty.comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.



Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

additionalType.label: additionalType
additionalType.comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

addressCountry.label: addressCountry
addressCountry.comment: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

addressLocality.label: addressLocality
addressLocality.comment: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

addressRegion.label: addressRegion
addressRegion.comment: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level Administrative division

advanceBookingRequirement.label: advanceBookingRequirement
advanceBookingRequirement.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

affiliation.label: affiliation
affiliation.comment: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

afterMedia.label: afterMedia
afterMedia.comment: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

agent.label: agent
agent.comment: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.

aggregateRating.label: aggregateRating
aggregateRating.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

albumProductionType.label: albumProductionType
albumProductionType.comment: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

albumReleaseType.label: albumReleaseType
albumReleaseType.comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

alignmentType.label: alignmentType
alignmentType.comment: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationalLevel'.

alternativeHeadline.label: alternativeHeadline
alternativeHeadline.comment: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

alumniOf.label: alumniOf
alumniOf.comment: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

amenityFeature.label: amenityFeature
amenityFeature.comment: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

amountOfThisGood.label: amountOfThisGood
amountOfThisGood.comment: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

annualPercentageRate.label: annualPercentageRate
annualPercentageRate.comment: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

answerCount.label: answerCount
answerCount.comment: The number of answers this question has received.

application.label: application
application.comment: An application that can complete the request.

applicationCategory.label: applicationCategory
applicationCategory.comment: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

applicationSubCategory.label: applicationSubCategory
applicationSubCategory.comment: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

applicationSuite.label: applicationSuite
applicationSuite.comment: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

appliesToDeliveryMethod.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
appliesToDeliveryMethod.comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

appliesToPaymentMethod.label: appliesToPaymentMethod
appliesToPaymentMethod.comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

area.label: area
area.comment: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

areaServed.label: areaServed
areaServed.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

arrivalAirport.label: arrivalAirport
arrivalAirport.comment: The airport where the flight terminates.

arrivalBusStop.label: arrivalBusStop
arrivalBusStop.comment: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

arrivalGate.label: arrivalGate
arrivalGate.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

arrivalPlatform.label: arrivalPlatform
arrivalPlatform.comment: The platform where the train arrives.

arrivalStation.label: arrivalStation
arrivalStation.comment: The station where the train trip ends.

arrivalTerminal.label: arrivalTerminal
arrivalTerminal.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

artEdition.label: artEdition
artEdition.comment: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

artMedium.label: artMedium
artMedium.comment: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

artform.label: artform
artform.comment: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

articleBody.label: articleBody
articleBody.comment: The actual body of the article.

articleSection.label: articleSection
articleSection.comment: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

artworkSurface.label: artworkSurface
artworkSurface.comment: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

assembly.label: assembly
assembly.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

associatedArticle.label: associatedArticle
associatedArticle.comment: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

associatedMedia.label: associatedMedia
associatedMedia.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

athlete.label: athlete
athlete.comment: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

attendee.label: attendee
attendee.comment: A person or organization attending the event.

audience.label: audience
audience.comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

audienceType.label: audienceType
audienceType.comment: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

authenticator.label: authenticator
authenticator.comment: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

author.label: author
author.comment: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

availability.label: availability
availability.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

availabilityEnds.label: availabilityEnds
availabilityEnds.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

availabilityStarts.label: availabilityStarts
availabilityStarts.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

availableAtOrFrom.label: availableAtOrFrom
availableAtOrFrom.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

availableChannel.label: availableChannel
availableChannel.comment: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

availableDeliveryMethod.label: availableDeliveryMethod
availableDeliveryMethod.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

availableFrom.label: availableFrom
availableFrom.comment: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

availableLanguage.label: availableLanguage
availableLanguage.comment: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage

availableOnDevice.label: availableOnDevice
availableOnDevice.comment: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

availableThrough.label: availableThrough
availableThrough.comment: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

award.label: award
award.comment: An award won by or for this item.

awards.label: awards
awards.comment: Awards won by or for this item.

awayTeam.label: awayTeam
awayTeam.comment: The away team in a sports event.

baseSalary.label: baseSalary
baseSalary.comment: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

bccRecipient.label: bccRecipient
bccRecipient.comment: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

bed.label: bed
bed.comment: The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

beforeMedia.label: beforeMedia
beforeMedia.comment: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

benefits.label: benefits
benefits.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

bestRating.label: bestRating
bestRating.comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

billingAddress.label: billingAddress
billingAddress.comment: The billing address for the order.

billingIncrement.label: billingIncrement
billingIncrement.comment: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

billingPeriod.label: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.comment: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

birthPlace.label: birthPlace
birthPlace.comment: The place where the person was born.

bitrate.label: bitrate
bitrate.comment: The bitrate of the media object.

blogPost.label: blogPost
blogPost.comment: A posting that is part of this blog.

blogPosts.label: blogPosts
blogPosts.comment: The postings that are part of this blog.

boardingGroup.label: boardingGroup
boardingGroup.comment: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

boardingPolicy.label: boardingPolicy
boardingPolicy.comment: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

bookingAgent.label: bookingAgent
bookingAgent.comment: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

bookingTime.label: bookingTime
bookingTime.comment: The date and time the reservation was booked.

borrower.label: borrower
borrower.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

box.label: box
box.comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

branchCode.label: branchCode
branchCode.comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.



For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

branchOf.label: branchOf
branchOf.comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical)branch.

brand.label: brand
brand.comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

breadcrumb.label: breadcrumb
breadcrumb.comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

broadcastAffiliateOf.label: broadcastAffiliateOf
broadcastAffiliateOf.comment: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

broadcastChannelId.label: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.comment: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

broadcastDisplayName.label: broadcastDisplayName
broadcastDisplayName.comment: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

broadcastFrequency.label: broadcastFrequency
broadcastFrequency.comment: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequences of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

broadcastFrequencyValue.label: broadcastFrequencyValue
broadcastFrequencyValue.comment: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

broadcastOfEvent.label: broadcastOfEvent
broadcastOfEvent.comment: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

broadcastServiceTier.label: broadcastServiceTier
broadcastServiceTier.comment: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

broadcastTimezone.label: broadcastTimezone
broadcastTimezone.comment: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts

broadcaster.label: broadcaster
broadcaster.comment: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

broker.label: broker
broker.comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

browserRequirements.label: browserRequirements
browserRequirements.comment: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

busName.label: busName
busName.comment: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

busNumber.label: busNumber
busNumber.comment: The unique identifier for the bus.

businessFunction.label: businessFunction
businessFunction.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

buyer.label: buyer
buyer.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

byArtist.label: byArtist
byArtist.comment: The artist that performed this album or recording.

candidate.label: candidate
candidate.comment: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

caption.label: caption
caption.comment: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the encodingFormat.

carbohydrateContent.label: carbohydrateContent
carbohydrateContent.comment: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

cargoVolume.label: cargoVolume
cargoVolume.comment:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.



Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet



Note: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

carrier.label: carrier
carrier.comment: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

carrierRequirements.label: carrierRequirements
carrierRequirements.comment: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

catalog.label: catalog
catalog.comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

catalogNumber.label: catalogNumber
catalogNumber.comment: The catalog number for the release.

category.label: category
category.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

ccRecipient.label: ccRecipient
ccRecipient.comment: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

character.label: character
character.comment: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

characterAttribute.label: characterAttribute
characterAttribute.comment: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

characterName.label: characterName
characterName.comment: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

checkinTime.label: checkinTime
checkinTime.comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

checkoutTime.label: checkoutTime
checkoutTime.comment: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

cholesterolContent.label: cholesterolContent
cholesterolContent.comment: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

circle.label: circle
circle.comment: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

citation.label: citation
citation.comment: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

claimReviewed.label: claimReviewed
claimReviewed.comment: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

clipNumber.label: clipNumber
clipNumber.comment: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

closes.label: closes
closes.comment: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

coach.label: coach
coach.comment: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

codeRepository.label: codeRepository
codeRepository.comment: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex).

codeSampleType.label: codeSampleType
codeSampleType.comment: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

collection.label: collection
collection.comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

commentCount.label: commentCount
commentCount.comment: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

commentTime.label: commentTime
commentTime.comment: The time at which the UserComment was made.

competitor.label: competitor
competitor.comment: A competitor in a sports event.

composer.label: composer
composer.comment: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

confirmationNumber.label: confirmationNumber
confirmationNumber.comment: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

contactOption.label: contactOption
contactOption.comment: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

contactPoint.label: contactPoint
contactPoint.comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

contactPoints.label: contactPoints
contactPoints.comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

contactType.label: contactType
contactType.comment: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

containedIn.label: containedIn
containedIn.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

containedInPlace.label: containedInPlace
containedInPlace.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

containsPlace.label: containsPlace
containsPlace.comment: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

containsSeason.label: containsSeason
containsSeason.comment: A season that is part of the media series.

contentLocation.label: contentLocation
contentLocation.comment: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

contentRating.label: contentRating
contentRating.comment: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

contentType.label: contentType
contentType.comment: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

contentUrl.label: contentUrl
contentUrl.comment: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

contributor.label: contributor
contributor.comment: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

cookTime.label: cookTime
cookTime.comment: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in ISO 8601 duration format.

cookingMethod.label: cookingMethod
cookingMethod.comment: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

copyrightHolder.label: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.comment: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

copyrightYear.label: copyrightYear
copyrightYear.comment: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

countriesNotSupported.label: countriesNotSupported
countriesNotSupported.comment: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

countriesSupported.label: countriesSupported
countriesSupported.comment: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

countryOfOrigin.label: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.comment: The country of the principal offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie or program.

course.label: course
course.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

courseCode.label: courseCode
courseCode.comment: The identifier for the Course used by the course provider (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

courseMode.label: courseMode
courseMode.comment: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

coursePrerequisites.label: coursePrerequisites
coursePrerequisites.comment: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another Course or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using AlignmentObject.

coverageEndTime.label: coverageEndTime
coverageEndTime.comment: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

coverageStartTime.label: coverageStartTime
coverageStartTime.comment: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

creator.label: creator
creator.comment: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

creditedTo.label: creditedTo
creditedTo.comment: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

cssSelector.label: cssSelector
cssSelector.comment: A CSS selector, e.g. of a SpeakableSpecification or WebPageElement. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

currenciesAccepted.label: currenciesAccepted
currenciesAccepted.comment:
The currency accepted.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

currency.label: currency
currency.comment:
The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

customer.label: customer
customer.comment: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

dataFeedElement.label: dataFeedElement
dataFeedElement.comment: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

dataset.label: dataset
dataset.comment: A dataset contained in this catalog.

datasetTimeInterval.label: datasetTimeInterval
datasetTimeInterval.comment: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

dateCreated.label: dateCreated
dateCreated.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

dateDeleted.label: dateDeleted
dateDeleted.comment: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

dateIssued.label: dateIssued
dateIssued.comment: The date the ticket was issued.

dateModified.label: dateModified
dateModified.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

datePosted.label: datePosted
datePosted.comment: Publication date of an online listing.

dateRead.label: dateRead
dateRead.comment: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

dateReceived.label: dateReceived
dateReceived.comment: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

dateSent.label: dateSent
dateSent.comment: The date/time at which the message was sent.

dateVehicleFirstRegistered.label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
dateVehicleFirstRegistered.comment: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

dateline.label: dateline
dateline.comment:
A dateline is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.



Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using locationCreated (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written). For location depicted or described in the content, use contentLocation.



Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

dayOfWeek.label: dayOfWeek
dayOfWeek.comment: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

deathPlace.label: deathPlace
deathPlace.comment: The place where the person died.

defaultValue.label: defaultValue
defaultValue.comment: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

deliveryLeadTime.label: deliveryLeadTime
deliveryLeadTime.comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

deliveryMethod.label: deliveryMethod
deliveryMethod.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

deliveryStatus.label: deliveryStatus
deliveryStatus.comment: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

department.label: department
department.comment: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

departureAirport.label: departureAirport
departureAirport.comment: The airport where the flight originates.

departureBusStop.label: departureBusStop
departureBusStop.comment: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

departureGate.label: departureGate
departureGate.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

departurePlatform.label: departurePlatform
departurePlatform.comment: The platform from which the train departs.

departureStation.label: departureStation
departureStation.comment: The station from which the train departs.

departureTerminal.label: departureTerminal
departureTerminal.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

dependencies.label: dependencies
dependencies.comment: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

device.label: device
device.comment: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

director.label: director
director.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

directors.label: directors
directors.comment: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

disambiguatingDescription.label: disambiguatingDescription
disambiguatingDescription.comment: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

discountCode.label: discountCode
discountCode.comment: Code used to redeem a discount.

discountCurrency.label: discountCurrency
discountCurrency.comment:
The currency of the discount.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

discusses.label: discusses
discusses.comment: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

discussionUrl.label: discussionUrl
discussionUrl.comment: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

dissolutionDate.label: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.comment: The date that this organization was dissolved.

distance.label: distance
distance.comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

distribution.label: distribution
distribution.comment: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

downloadUrl.label: downloadUrl
downloadUrl.comment: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

downvoteCount.label: downvoteCount
downvoteCount.comment: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

driveWheelConfiguration.label: driveWheelConfiguration
driveWheelConfiguration.comment: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

dropoffLocation.label: dropoffLocation
dropoffLocation.comment: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

dropoffTime.label: dropoffTime
dropoffTime.comment: When a rental car can be dropped off.

duns.label: duns
duns.comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

duration.label: duration
duration.comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

durationOfWarranty.label: durationOfWarranty
durationOfWarranty.comment: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

duringMedia.label: duringMedia
duringMedia.comment: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

editor.label: editor
editor.comment: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

educationalAlignment.label: educationalAlignment
educationalAlignment.comment: An alignment to an established educational framework.

educationalCredentialAwarded.label: educationalCredentialAwarded
educationalCredentialAwarded.comment: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

educationalFramework.label: educationalFramework
educationalFramework.comment: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

educationalUse.label: educationalUse
educationalUse.comment: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

elevation.label: elevation
elevation.comment: The elevation of a location (WGS 84). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNITOFMEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

eligibleCustomerType.label: eligibleCustomerType
eligibleCustomerType.comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

eligibleDuration.label: eligibleDuration
eligibleDuration.comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

eligibleQuantity.label: eligibleQuantity
eligibleQuantity.comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

eligibleRegion.label: eligibleRegion
eligibleRegion.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.



See also ineligibleRegion.

eligibleTransactionVolume.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
eligibleTransactionVolume.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

embedUrl.label: embedUrl
embedUrl.comment: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.

employmentType.label: employmentType
employmentType.comment: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

encodesCreativeWork.label: encodesCreativeWork
encodesCreativeWork.comment: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

encoding.label: encoding
encoding.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

encodingFormat.label: encodingFormat
encodingFormat.comment:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).



In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.



Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

encodingType.label: encodingType
encodingType.comment: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

encodings.label: encodings
encodings.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

endDate.label: endDate
endDate.comment: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

endTime.label: endTime
endTime.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.



Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

endorsee.label: endorsee
endorsee.comment: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

entertainmentBusiness.label: entertainmentBusiness
entertainmentBusiness.comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

episode.label: episode
episode.comment: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

episodeNumber.label: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.comment: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

episodes.label: episodes
episodes.comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

equal.label: equal
equal.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

error.label: error
error.comment: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

estimatedCost.label: estimatedCost
estimatedCost.comment: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

estimatedFlightDuration.label: estimatedFlightDuration
estimatedFlightDuration.comment: The estimated time the flight will take.

estimatedSalary.label: estimatedSalary
estimatedSalary.comment: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

event.label: event
event.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

eventStatus.label: eventStatus
eventStatus.comment: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

events.label: events
events.comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

exampleOfWork.label: exampleOfWork
exampleOfWork.comment: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

executableLibraryName.label: executableLibraryName
executableLibraryName.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

exerciseCourse.label: exerciseCourse
exerciseCourse.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

expectedArrivalFrom.label: expectedArrivalFrom
expectedArrivalFrom.comment: The earliest date the package may arrive.

expectedArrivalUntil.label: expectedArrivalUntil
expectedArrivalUntil.comment: The latest date the package may arrive.

expectsAcceptanceOf.label: expectsAcceptanceOf
expectsAcceptanceOf.comment: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

experienceRequirements.label: experienceRequirements
experienceRequirements.comment: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

expires.label: expires
expires.comment: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

familyName.label: familyName
familyName.comment: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

fatContent.label: fatContent
fatContent.comment: The number of grams of fat.

featureList.label: featureList
featureList.comment: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

feesAndCommissionsSpecification.label: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
feesAndCommissionsSpecification.comment: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

fiberContent.label: fiberContent
fiberContent.comment: The number of grams of fiber.

fileFormat.label: fileFormat
fileFormat.comment: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

fileSize.label: fileSize
fileSize.comment: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

firstPerformance.label: firstPerformance
firstPerformance.comment: The date and place the work was first performed.

flightNumber.label: flightNumber
flightNumber.comment: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

floorSize.label: floorSize
floorSize.comment: The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

followee.label: followee
followee.comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

follows.label: follows
follows.comment: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

foodEstablishment.label: foodEstablishment
foodEstablishment.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

foodEvent.label: foodEvent
foodEvent.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

founder.label: founder
founder.comment: A person who founded this organization.

founders.label: founders
founders.comment: A person who founded this organization.

foundingDate.label: foundingDate
foundingDate.comment: The date that this organization was founded.

foundingLocation.label: foundingLocation
foundingLocation.comment: The place where the Organization was founded.

free.label: free
free.comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

fromLocation.label: fromLocation
fromLocation.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

fuelConsumption.label: fuelConsumption
fuelConsumption.comment:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).



  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

fuelEfficiency.label: fuelEfficiency
fuelEfficiency.comment:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).



  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

fuelType.label: fuelType
fuelType.comment: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

funder.label: funder
funder.comment: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

game.label: game
game.comment: Video game which is played on this server.

gameItem.label: gameItem
gameItem.comment: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

gameLocation.label: gameLocation
gameLocation.comment: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

gamePlatform.label: gamePlatform
gamePlatform.comment: The electronic systems used to play video games.

gameServer.label: gameServer
gameServer.comment: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

genre.label: genre
genre.comment: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

geo.label: geo
geo.comment: The geo coordinates of the place.

geoContains.label: geoContains
geoContains.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

geoCoveredBy.label: geoCoveredBy
geoCoveredBy.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

geoCovers.label: geoCovers
geoCovers.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

geoCrosses.label: geoCrosses
geoCrosses.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

geoDisjoint.label: geoDisjoint
geoDisjoint.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

geoEquals.label: geoEquals
geoEquals.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

geoIntersects.label: geoIntersects
geoIntersects.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

geoMidpoint.label: geoMidpoint
geoMidpoint.comment: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

geoOverlaps.label: geoOverlaps
geoOverlaps.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

geoRadius.label: geoRadius
geoRadius.comment: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

geoTouches.label: geoTouches
geoTouches.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

geoWithin.label: geoWithin
geoWithin.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

geographicArea.label: geographicArea
geographicArea.comment: The geographic area associated with the audience.

givenName.label: givenName
givenName.comment: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

globalLocationNumber.label: globalLocationNumber
globalLocationNumber.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

grantee.label: grantee
grantee.comment: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

greater.label: greater
greater.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

greaterOrEqual.label: greaterOrEqual
greaterOrEqual.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

gtin12.label: gtin12
gtin12.comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

gtin13.label: gtin13
gtin13.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

gtin14.label: gtin14
gtin14.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

gtin8.label: gtin8
gtin8.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

hasBroadcastChannel.label: hasBroadcastChannel
hasBroadcastChannel.comment: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

hasCourseInstance.label: hasCourseInstance
hasCourseInstance.comment: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

hasDeliveryMethod.label: hasDeliveryMethod
hasDeliveryMethod.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

hasDigitalDocumentPermission.label: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
hasDigitalDocumentPermission.comment: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

hasMap.label: hasMap
hasMap.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

hasMenu.label: hasMenu
hasMenu.comment: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

hasMenuItem.label: hasMenuItem
hasMenuItem.comment: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

hasMenuSection.label: hasMenuSection
hasMenuSection.comment: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

hasOccupation.label: hasOccupation
hasOccupation.comment: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

hasOfferCatalog.label: hasOfferCatalog
hasOfferCatalog.comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

hasPOS.label: hasPOS
hasPOS.comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

hasPart.label: hasPart
hasPart.comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

highPrice.label: highPrice
highPrice.comment:
The highest price of all offers available.



Usage guidelines:



  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

homeLocation.label: homeLocation
homeLocation.comment: A contact location for a person's residence.

homeTeam.label: homeTeam
homeTeam.comment: The home team in a sports event.

honorificPrefix.label: honorificPrefix
honorificPrefix.comment: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

honorificSuffix.label: honorificSuffix
honorificSuffix.comment: An honorific suffix preceding a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.

hostingOrganization.label: hostingOrganization
hostingOrganization.comment: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

hoursAvailable.label: hoursAvailable
hoursAvailable.comment: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

httpMethod.label: httpMethod
httpMethod.comment: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

iataCode.label: iataCode
iataCode.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

identifier.label: identifier
identifier.comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.

image.label: image
image.comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

inAlbum.label: inAlbum
inAlbum.comment: The album to which this recording belongs.

inLanguage.label: inLanguage
inLanguage.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

inPlaylist.label: inPlaylist
inPlaylist.comment: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

incentiveCompensation.label: incentiveCompensation
incentiveCompensation.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

incentives.label: incentives
incentives.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

includedComposition.label: includedComposition
includedComposition.comment: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

includedDataCatalog.label: includedDataCatalog
includedDataCatalog.comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

includedInDataCatalog.label: includedInDataCatalog
includedInDataCatalog.comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

includesObject.label: includesObject
includesObject.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

industry.label: industry
industry.comment: The industry associated with the job position.

ingredients.label: ingredients
ingredients.comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

installUrl.label: installUrl
installUrl.comment: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

instructor.label: instructor
instructor.comment: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the CourseInstance.

instrument.label: instrument
instrument.comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.

interactionCount.label: interactionCount
interactionCount.comment: This property is deprecated, alongside the UserInteraction types on which it depended.

interactionService.label: interactionService
interactionService.comment: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

interactionStatistic.label: interactionStatistic
interactionStatistic.comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

interactionType.label: interactionType
interactionType.comment: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use LikeAction. For down votes use DislikeAction. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

interactivityType.label: interactivityType
interactivityType.comment: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

interestRate.label: interestRate
interestRate.comment: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

inventoryLevel.label: inventoryLevel
inventoryLevel.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

isAccessibleForFree.label: isAccessibleForFree
isAccessibleForFree.comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.label: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

isBasedOn.label: isBasedOn
isBasedOn.comment: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaption.

isBasedOnUrl.label: isBasedOnUrl
isBasedOnUrl.comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

isConsumableFor.label: isConsumableFor
isConsumableFor.comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

isFamilyFriendly.label: isFamilyFriendly
isFamilyFriendly.comment: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

isGift.label: isGift
isGift.comment: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

isLiveBroadcast.label: isLiveBroadcast
isLiveBroadcast.comment: True is the broadcast is of a live event.

isPartOf.label: isPartOf
isPartOf.comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

isRelatedTo.label: isRelatedTo
isRelatedTo.comment: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

isSimilarTo.label: isSimilarTo
isSimilarTo.comment: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

isVariantOf.label: isVariantOf
isVariantOf.comment: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

isicV4.label: isicV4
isicV4.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

isrcCode.label: isrcCode
isrcCode.comment: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

issn.label: issn
issn.comment: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

issueNumber.label: issueNumber
issueNumber.comment: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

issuedBy.label: issuedBy
issuedBy.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

issuedThrough.label: issuedThrough
issuedThrough.comment: The service through with the permit was granted.

iswcCode.label: iswcCode
iswcCode.comment: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

item.label: item
item.comment: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists')’.

itemCondition.label: itemCondition
itemCondition.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

itemListElement.label: itemListElement
itemListElement.comment:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.



Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.



Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

itemListOrder.label: itemListOrder
itemListOrder.comment: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

itemOffered.label: itemOffered
itemOffered.comment: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using businessFunction, e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

itemReviewed.label: itemReviewed
itemReviewed.comment: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

jobBenefits.label: jobBenefits
jobBenefits.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

jobLocation.label: jobLocation
jobLocation.comment: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

keywords.label: keywords
keywords.comment: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

knownVehicleDamages.label: knownVehicleDamages
knownVehicleDamages.comment: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

knows.label: knows
knows.comment: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

landlord.label: landlord
landlord.comment: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

language.label: language
language.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

lastReviewed.label: lastReviewed
lastReviewed.comment: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

latitude.label: latitude
latitude.comment: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

learningResourceType.label: learningResourceType
learningResourceType.comment: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

legalName.label: legalName
legalName.comment: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

leiCode.label: leiCode
leiCode.comment: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

lender.label: lender
lender.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

lesser.label: lesser
lesser.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

lesserOrEqual.label: lesserOrEqual
lesserOrEqual.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

license.label: license
license.comment: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

line.label: line
line.comment: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

loanTerm.label: loanTerm
loanTerm.comment: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

location.label: location
location.comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

locationCreated.label: locationCreated
locationCreated.comment: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

lodgingUnitDescription.label: lodgingUnitDescription
lodgingUnitDescription.comment: A full description of the lodging unit.

lodgingUnitType.label: lodgingUnitType
lodgingUnitType.comment: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

longitude.label: longitude
longitude.comment: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

loser.label: loser
loser.comment: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

lowPrice.label: lowPrice
lowPrice.comment:
The lowest price of all offers available.



Usage guidelines:



  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

lyricist.label: lyricist
lyricist.comment: The person who wrote the words.

mainContentOfPage.label: mainContentOfPage
mainContentOfPage.comment: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

mainEntity.label: mainEntity
mainEntity.comment: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

mainEntityOfPage.label: mainEntityOfPage
mainEntityOfPage.comment: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See background notes for details.

makesOffer.label: makesOffer
makesOffer.comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

map.label: map
map.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

mapType.label: mapType
mapType.comment: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

maps.label: maps
maps.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

material.label: material
material.comment: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

maxPrice.label: maxPrice
maxPrice.comment: The highest price if the price is a range.

maxValue.label: maxValue
maxValue.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

maximumAttendeeCapacity.label: maximumAttendeeCapacity
maximumAttendeeCapacity.comment: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

mealService.label: mealService
mealService.comment: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

member.label: member
member.comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

memberOf.label: memberOf
memberOf.comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

membershipNumber.label: membershipNumber
membershipNumber.comment: A unique identifier for the membership.

mentions.label: mentions
mentions.comment: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

menu.label: menu
menu.comment: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

menuAddOn.label: menuAddOn
menuAddOn.comment: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

messageAttachment.label: messageAttachment
messageAttachment.comment: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

mileageFromOdometer.label: mileageFromOdometer
mileageFromOdometer.comment:
The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.



Typical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

minPrice.label: minPrice
minPrice.comment: The lowest price if the price is a range.

minValue.label: minValue
minValue.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

minimumPaymentDue.label: minimumPaymentDue
minimumPaymentDue.comment: The minimum payment required at this time.

model.label: model
model.comment: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

modifiedTime.label: modifiedTime
modifiedTime.comment: The date and time the reservation was modified.

mpn.label: mpn
mpn.comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

multipleValues.label: multipleValues
multipleValues.comment: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

musicArrangement.label: musicArrangement
musicArrangement.comment: An arrangement derived from the composition.

musicCompositionForm.label: musicCompositionForm
musicCompositionForm.comment: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

musicGroupMember.label: musicGroupMember
musicGroupMember.comment: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

musicReleaseFormat.label: musicReleaseFormat
musicReleaseFormat.comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

musicalKey.label: musicalKey
musicalKey.comment: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

naics.label: naics
naics.comment: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

namedPosition.label: namedPosition
namedPosition.comment: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

netWorth.label: netWorth
netWorth.comment: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

nextItem.label: nextItem
nextItem.comment: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

nonEqual.label: nonEqual
nonEqual.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

numAdults.label: numAdults
numAdults.comment: The number of adults staying in the unit.

numChildren.label: numChildren
numChildren.comment: The number of children staying in the unit.

numTracks.label: numTracks
numTracks.comment: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

numberOfAirbags.label: numberOfAirbags
numberOfAirbags.comment: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

numberOfAxles.label: numberOfAxles
numberOfAxles.comment:
The number of axles.



Typical unit code(s): C62

numberOfBeds.label: numberOfBeds
numberOfBeds.comment: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

numberOfDoors.label: numberOfDoors
numberOfDoors.comment:
The number of doors.



Typical unit code(s): C62

numberOfEmployees.label: numberOfEmployees
numberOfEmployees.comment: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

numberOfEpisodes.label: numberOfEpisodes
numberOfEpisodes.comment: The number of episodes in this season or series.

numberOfForwardGears.label: numberOfForwardGears
numberOfForwardGears.comment:
The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.



Typical unit code(s): C62

numberOfItems.label: numberOfItems
numberOfItems.comment: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

numberOfPages.label: numberOfPages
numberOfPages.comment: The number of pages in the book.

numberOfPlayers.label: numberOfPlayers
numberOfPlayers.comment: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

numberOfPreviousOwners.label: numberOfPreviousOwners
numberOfPreviousOwners.comment:
The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.



Typical unit code(s): C62

numberOfRooms.label: numberOfRooms
numberOfRooms.comment: The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

numberOfSeasons.label: numberOfSeasons
numberOfSeasons.comment: The number of seasons in this series.

numberedPosition.label: numberedPosition
numberedPosition.comment: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

nutrition.label: nutrition
nutrition.comment: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

object.label: object
object.comment: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

occupancy.label: occupancy
occupancy.comment: The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

occupationLocation.label: occupationLocation
occupationLocation.comment: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

offerCount.label: offerCount
offerCount.comment: The number of offers for the product.

offeredBy.label: offeredBy
offeredBy.comment: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

offers.label: offers
offers.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.
